      "status_detail": "Version 4 head discovery, EDID make/model/serial identity, complete DRM mode advertisement and selection, hotplug lifecycles, stale-serial cancellation, complete test/apply transactions, positions, fractional scales, and native DRM enable/disable are implemented for Kanshi. Mode and scale changes update scanout buffers, logical geometry, rendering, input bounds, wl_output, xdg-output, fractional-scale, layer-shell, and River output state, with transactional rollback on failure. Unsupported custom modes, transforms, and adaptive sync are rejected. The privileged global is hidden from sandboxed security-context clients."
